commitResults.messageBody:
Allow classifying contacts as favourites allow us to search up
commonly used contacts with ease.

Let's
* Add command: allow an optional input prefix when creating contacts to classify
  the contact as favourite
* Edit command: modify existing contact to either classify them as favourite or
  not favourite
* Find command: improve search to allow finding of favourites contacts, able to
  search together with other valid prefixes

Currently, editing a favourite contact to classify them as favourite
works as a valid edit procedure, similarly for classfying non
favourite contact as non favourite.
Updated `generateContactInformation()` method to also correctly display "isFavourite" status in `view` page

commitResults.messageBody:
Implement the `SwitchCommand` which:
- Switches the session to a new profile if a valid profile name is
  provided.
- Lists all available profiles if no profile name is provided and
  other profiles exist.
- Prevents switching to the current active profile and notifies
  the user if the requested profile is the same as the active one.

commitResults.messageTitle: Refactor Help Command to display updated guides
commitResults.messageBody:
The current help command uses hard-coded help messages for each
command in the system.

This approach causes frequent inconsistencies when commands are
added or modified, as the help messages are not synchronized.

Refactor the help command to use the MESSAGE_USAGE string from
each command, ensuring that the help information remains
consistent and up-to-date.

Minor adjustments are made to some Command classes to ensure
uniform message formatting across the system. Also, minor visual
improvements were made to the help window for better user
experience.

commitResults.messageTitle: Add `deleteProfile` command for deleting existing profiles
commitResults.messageBody:
This commit introduces a `deleteProfile` command that allows users
to delete profiles from the application. Validations ensure that
the system remains stable even if users manually modify files in
the data directory to an invalid structure.

Advanced users can now also import profiles into the `data/` directory
manually and use the `switch` command to access them.

Minor adjustments were made to the test setup to ensure temporary
files are created within a `data/` subdirectory, aligning with
the new validation requirements.

commitResults.messageBody: Update help window to display basic command usage

Current iteration of AB3 does not support the accessing of certain
contacts to view all information / information that may not be
displayed on the Person Card component.

As such, the user may be unable to access or even view other
critical information of their contact of interest.

Let's incorporate that functionality, allowing users to view
ALL contact information of the specified contact with the specified
telegram handle.

Currently, iew updates the command output segment, while keeping
the list of contacts visible.

As the number of fields for each contact grows, the lack of vertical
space in that segment means the view command serves little purpose in
allowing the user to view all the information of the specified contact.

Let's hide the list of contacts, and display a new page below the command
output section that showcases all the existing (and future) information
of the specified contact whenever the iew command is called.

commitResults.messageTitle: Add GUI changes to list of contacts
commitResults.messageBody:
Contacts can't be seen if they've attended the CCA session for the
current date.

This makes it hard for users to expediently see which members are not
present for the CCA session at one glance. As such, they must
individually iew each and every member to note their attendance.

Let's add a visual GUI component in the list that indicates if that
particular contact has been marked as present for the current
session.
Add list contacts with role "Member" command and

Attendance status shows up indiscriminately for each contact.

May not be necessary for contacts which are not members of
the CCA.

Let's leverage on the special Member role to display the
attendance status only for contacts that are members. This
includes both the list view, as well as the contact info
when using the iew command.

Favourite contacts cannot be visually differentiated from normal contacts

This renders the 'favourite' feature useless, as non-favourite contacts
are basically the same as favourite contacts.

Let's update the UI of 'favourite' contacts to make them stand out more.
